"a.令人喜悦的；欣然同意的 【英】 adj. 令人喜悦的(pleasing );欣然同意的(ready to agree) 【考】 反义词：irritable( 坏脾气的) adj. 令人喜悦的 = pleasing; 欣然同意的 【例】Are you agreeable to his suggestion? 你同意他的建议吗? make oneself agreeable to sb 热情招待某人, 与某人和睦相处 【反】irritable(adj 易怒的; 急躁的) 【记】agree 令人同意的 agreeable (adj.)  late 14c., ""to one's liking,"" from Old French agreable (12c., Modern French agréable) ""pleasing, in agreement, consenting, thankful,"" from agreer ""to please"" (see agree). Related: Agreeably. To do the agreeable (1825) was to ""act in a courteous manner."""
